The faerie leveller, or, King Charles his leveller descried and deciphered in Queene Elizabeths dayes by her poet laureat Edmond Spenser, in his unparaleld poeme entituled, The faerie qveene, a lively representation of our times. Faerie queen. Selections Spenser, Edmund, 1552?-1599.
11 p.
s.n.], [London : 1648.
In verse. An extract from The faerie queene, book 5, canto 2, stanzas 29-54, with a preface identifying Artegal with King Charles, the giant leveller with Cromwell, etc.--NUC pre-1956 imprints. Place of publication suggested by NUC pre-1956 imprints. Reproduction of original in the Huntington Library.
